City: edinburgh, rome, boston, san-francisco
The people use 4 different means of transport: boat, subway, quad-bike, car
The people prefer 4 different types of sport: ice-hockey, rugby, soccer, volleyball
 1. the person traveling to rome is on the far right##1
 2. the person traveling to san-francisco is the person playing scrabble##1
 3. the person driving the boat is on the right of the person who's sport is volleyball##1
 4. the person who's sport is ice-hockey is on the far left##1
 5. the person traveling to san-francisco is the person driving the subway##1
 6. the person driving the car is on the right of the person who's sport is ice-hockey##1
 7. the person traveling to rome is the person playing monopoly##1
 8. the person traveling to edinburgh is on the right of the person traveling to san-francisco##1
 9. the person playing scrabble is on the left of the person who's sport is rugby##1
10. the person playing snooker is between the person driving the boat and the person playing billiard##2

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |    2    |      3       |       4        |
| Game           | scrabble  | billiard | snooker     | monopoly |
| City   | san-francisco | edinburgh  | boston | rome       |
| Transport           | subway       | car    | quad-bike      | boat           |
| Sport         | ice-hockey | rugby   | volleyball   | soccer         |

